:INFO
Parts List for a DIY E-Bike Conversion
Specific parts and sourcing guidance for a reliable 500W rear hub motor e-bike conversion suitable for urban commuting.

:TASK
[ ] Rear hub motor kit 500W 48V with laced wheel and tire
[ ] 48V 13Ah lithium ion battery with BMS and XT60 connector
[ ] KT or Sabvoton controller matched to motor voltage
[ ] LCD display panel showing speed, battery, and assist level
[ ] Thumb throttle or twist throttle per preference
[ ] Brake levers with motor cutoff switches
[ ] Torque arm for rear dropout to prevent axle rotation
[ ] Anderson or XT60 connectors for battery connection
[ ] Cable ties and spiral cable wrap for wiring management
[ ] Multimeter for verifying connections before powering on

:NOTE
Buy motor kit and battery as a matched set from a single supplier when possible. Voltage mismatches between battery and controller are the most common cause of conversion failures and component damage.

